================ Algorithm Patterns + Memory Tricks =================

Pattern                  | Real-Life Analogy                    | Big-O
-------------------------|-------------------------------------|-----------------
1) Frequency Counter      | Counting items in a bag             | O(n)
   - Imagine: “How many red marbles vs blue marbles?” 
   - Compare counts instead of checking every pair

2) Multiple Pointers      | Two people walking toward each other | O(n)
   - Imagine: “Left and right friends meeting in a hallway”
   - Move pointers based on target sum or condition

3) Sliding Window         | Rolling window on a street view     | O(n)
   - Imagine: “Photograph a moving section of street”  
   - Don’t recount everything, just update the window

4) Divide & Conquer       | Cutting a cake into pieces          | O(log n) – O(n log n)
   - Imagine: “Find a cherry in a layered cake by cutting in half repeatedly”
   - Solve smaller pieces, then combine

5) Recursion / Backtracking | Maze exploration / tree climbing  | O(n) – O(2ⁿ)
   - Imagine: “At each fork, choose a path; backtrack if wrong”
   - Explore all possibilities in a branching path

---------------- Tips ----------------
- Think **real-life analogy first**, code second  
- Patterns often map 1-to-1 with problem type  
- Big-O growth = how “hard” the real-world analogy scales  

